Solar Boat Twente
on Thursday

We would like to thank Momapack Maatverpakkingen who has been our partner for the last 1.5 years! Momapack provided us with specially designed foams for our hydrofoils and propulsion system. These parts are very essential to our solar boat in order to move forward and fly above the water. Therefore it is very important to protect them while transporting from one place to another.

Solar Boat Twente
about a month ago

Yesterday was a busy day but, above all, an amazing experience for us as a team! After we fixed the leak, we were able to finish the other two races without any problems! During the sprint we were even able to reach a speed of 32 km/h! Even though we finshed overall fourth, we are very proud of what we have accomplished after only one week of testing. And we're very happy that we have reached our goal, to build a trustworthy boat. A solid base for the next team, to make her sail even better!

Solar Boat Twente
about a month ago

RACE UPDATE
Unfortunately, early on in the endurance race we encountered water leaking into our right driver. We were unable to pump all of the water out of the boat during the race. Therefore, we had to pull the boat out of the water to fix the leak, making it impossible for us to finish the race. Luckily, we were able to fix the leak after some good and hard teamwork. Just now we were able to participate and finish in the match race, where we became third! In less than one hour we will start with the sprint race to finish the day!

Last Friday we were finally able to test our boat in the water! It was an amazing moment for us to see the Twentsch Pegasus sail on the water! 🤩 Even though we had some minor technical issues, we were able to do some successful back and forth testing! Luckily, the problems were easy to fix. So, this week you can also find us on the water in order to prepare the boat for the race on the Ketelmeer next Monday!

Solar Boat Twente
about 2 months ago

RACE ANNOUNCEMENT
More than one week after we revealed the Twentsch Pegasus, we have some exciting news! Since all of our races were cancelled, we didn’t get the opportunity to compare our boat with others. That’s why we will race against TU Delft Solar Boat Team and Sunflare Solarteam at the Ketelmeer in Flevoland on the 17th of August! This way we can test our boats together on efficiency, speed and maneuverability! We will provide you that day with lots of information and footage so you can follow us online!
We are excited about the race and working hard to get our boat ready for this day! More information will follow soon!

Solar Boat Twente
about 3 months ago

Last week we were finally able to pick up our electric motor!! This part makes sure our propellor can spin so we are able to move forward in the water. Most of the time the motor is located in the hull, but in our boat it is located in the nacelle. By using a so-called pod-motor we lose very little energy and the motor is automatically cooled by the water. Thanks Advanced Electromagnetics BV for producing this important part of our boat!

Solar Boat Twente
about 3 months ago

Maybe you already saw it in our stories, but last week we could finally pick up our solar panels! We can now connect the panels to the boat so we can soon use them to generate power for our boat! These panels consist of SunPower solar cells, which have an efficiency of 24.8%. The lamination of our cells, developed by MitoSolar, is specially designed to be super light, while it still protects the cells from the outside environment. In total, our deck only weighs 6 kg! 🤩 Thanks to our partners, like Solarstell, we are able to afford these high-quality panels!

Solar Boat Twente
about 3 months ago

Yesterday, we received some unfortunate news about the last race weekend of the season. The Solar Sport One organization made the hard decision to cancel the race that would have taken place on the 4th and 5th of September due to the coronavirus. It would not be safe or allowed to organize such a big event. They have looked into other options but unfortunately, they were not able to find an alternative that meets the requirements. Nevertheless, we are working hard to be able to sail as soon as we can! We are looking forward to it!
